   <mods:titleInfo>
      <mods:title>[Letter] 1808 Jul. 7, Talassee [Alabama, to] Benjamin Hawkins / Hopohuilthlu Miceo</mods:title>
   </mods:titleInfo>
   <mods:abstract>This is a copy of a letter to Colonel Benjamin Hawkins from the Creek Chief Hopohuilthlu Miceo, dated July 7, 1808. Hawkins is the U.S.'s Agent for Indian Affairs south of the Ohio River. Miceo is writing in regards to an attack by some Creeks on their American neighbors. Miceo wants Hawkins to assure President Jefferson that the Creeks will find out and punish the guilty parties.</mods:abstract>
